The paper deals with the problem of single-image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method, PULSE, uses a generative model and explores the latent space to generate high-resolution images, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of high-dimensional Gaussians to restrict the search space, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on face super-resolution, which is a subfield of computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
